    "The chain rule starts at the final layer and moves backwards until it reaches the initial layer.",
    "This allows the derivatives of the initial layers to be determined.",
    "Mode-collapseWhen the generator creates the same visuals or a miniscule proportion of the training visuals, mode-collapse arises.",
    "A successful generator should produce many training-imagelike images in all categories.",
    "When the discriminator cannot identify fake images, mode collapse occurs and the generator continues to create identical images to deceive it."
